        "subject": "LU-11432 lnet: Assign specific values to enum constants",
        "message": "LU-11432 lnet: Assign specific values to enum constants\n\nThe enum constants in lnet-types.h are automatically\nenumerated from 0. This can break the network\nprotocol compatibility if mistakenly a new\nvalues is inserted or a value is deleted in the\nmiddle of the list.\n\nThis patch also adds a new enum struct lnet_md_options\nto pack all the lnet MD options together.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Aryan Gupta <argupta@ddn.com>\nChange-Id: Ifce3096cdec84bb7192c7a669f6f07b0f4a19ac7\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
